summary: This is an FBI Evidence of Custody form for electronic surveillance (ELSUR) materials, likely related to intercepts in the Epstein case. It indicates the transfer of magnetic tape evidence for permanent storage, with references to Title III intercepts and consensual monitoring.
keyFacts: Document is an FBI Evidence of Custody form for electronic surveillance (ELSUR) materials.
References Title III court-authorized intercepts and consensual monitoring intercepts.
Indicates magnetic tape evidence was transferred for permanent storage.
Form includes fields for intercept date, place, and agent/supervisor signatures, but specific details are not fully legible in the provided text.
